                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1va">Fols. 1va-6</locus>vb, 126va-127va: Treatise on love to God and people, and on guarding the faith, addressed to monks (unidentified).<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 1v: መቅደም፡ ኵሉ፡ አፍቅሮ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ አምላክከ፡ በኵሉ፡ ልብከ፡ ወበኵሉ፡ ነፍስከ፡...</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The text continues from fol. 6vb into fol. 126va; it has been corrected in a contemporary hand.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#124ra">Fols. 124ra-126</locus>ra: Tǝrgwame śǝnä fǝṭrät “Commentary on the Beauty of Creation”.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 124ra: ትርጓሜ: ኦሪት፡ ብሂል፡ ፍትሕ፡ ወሥርዐት: ወዜና፡ ይትበሃል፡…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The text is written in a hand which is contemporary and similar to the main hand. It has been checked for errors and corrected by another hand. For a similar text s. Mss. MAKM-014 and THMR-018.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#126ra">Fol. 126ra</locus>-va: Excerpt from the Gospel of Matthew (Mt. 5: 1-11).<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#127va">Fol. 127va</locus>-vb: Excerpt from Mälkʾa Śǝllase (“Image of Trinity”). <q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 127va: አልብየ፡ ባእደ፡ ዘእንበሌክሙ፡ አምላከ፤ አብል፡ አንሰ፡ በልብየ: ነግሐ: ወሠርከ። ሥሉስ: ቅዱስ፡ ዘአልብክሙ፡ ተውሰከ። በሉኒ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ሰረይነ፡ ለከ፡ ኃጢአተ፡ ኵሎ፡ ዘገበርከ፡…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title of the work, ፊልክስዮስ, and the internal number of the monastic library (250) are written on fol. 1r. &#xD;
- Tämälläs-sign, in the shape of a cross, indicating the place where the omission written in the margin, in a secondary hand, belongs: fol. 30vb l.12.&#xD;
-  Corrections over erasure, in the main hand: e.g., fols.  13ra, 14va, 16rab, 21vb, 23vab, 33rab, 37va, 49va, 60va, 77ra, 97va, 109rab.&#xD;
- Erasures marked with two thin lines: fols. 15ra, 15va, 21vb, 22ra, 45ra, 55ra, 66ra, 106vb, 107ra.&#xD;
- Erasures: 14vb, 17ra, 26va, 28va, 91rb, 94va, 109vb.</item>
